public final class MapsEngineLayer

A MapsEngineLayer allows you to display data from Google Maps Engine.

Public Methods

public boolean equals (Object other)

public MapsEngineLayerInfo getLayerInfo ()

Gets the info set for this Maps Engine layer.

Returns
  • the layerId of the Maps Engine layer.

public float getZIndex ()

Gets the zIndex of this Maps Engine overlay.

Returns
  • the zIndex of the Maps Engine overlay.

public int hashCode ()

public boolean isDefaultUiEnabled ()

Returns whether the default UI is enabled or disabled for this Maps Engine layer.

Returns
  • true if the default UI is enabled, false if it is not.

public boolean isVisible ()

Gets the visibility of this Maps Engine overlay. Note that this does not return whether the tile overlay is actually within the screen's viewport, but whether it will be drawn if it is contained in the screen's viewport.

Returns
  • this Maps Engine overlay's visibility.

public void remove ()

Removes this maps engine overlay from the map.

public void setDefaultUiEnabled (boolean enabled)

Specifies whether or not to show the default infocard UI for this Maps Engine layer. The default is true.

public void setVisible (boolean visible)

Sets the visibility of this Maps Engine overlay. When not visible, a Maps Engine overlay is not drawn, but it keeps all its other properties.

Parameters
visible if true, then the Maps Engine overlay is visible; if false, it is not.

public void setZIndex (float zIndex)

Sets the zIndex of this Maps Engine overlay. See the documentation at the top of this class for more information.

Parameters
zIndex the zIndex of this Maps Engine overlay.
